  "prompt": "What are Top 10 worst black Friday disasters?",
  "response": "Here are 10 notable Black Friday disasters:\n\n1. Walmart Trampling (2008)\n- Employee Jdimytai Damour was trampled to death\n- Crowds broke down doors and stampeded into store\n- Multiple people injured\n\n2. Valley Stream, NY Walmart Incident\n- Customer killed during aggressive shopping rush\n- Shoppers overwhelmed security\n- Resulted in significant legal consequences\n\n3. Black Friday Shooting at Toys R Us (2010)\n- Two groups engaged in fatal shooting\n- Occurred in California store\n- Multiple people wounded\n\n4. Target Shooting (2018)\n- Shooting occurred during Black Friday shopping\n- Caused panic and store evacuation\n- Shoppers rushed to safety\n\n5. Shopping Mall Brawls\n- Multiple physical fights between shoppers\n- Disputes over merchandise and limited stock\n- Police intervention required\n\n6. Online Website Crashes\n- Major retailers' websites frequently crash\n- Customers unable to complete purchases\n- Significant financial losses for companies\n\n7. Birmingham, Alabama Mall Shooting (2021)\n- Multiple shootings caused mass panic\n- Teenagers involved in violent confrontation\n- Mall evacuation and temporary closure\n\n8. Electronic Store Stampedes\n- Customers rush for discounted electronics\n- Pushing, shoving, and potential injuries\n- Security challenges\n\n9. Parking Lot Confrontations\n- Fights over parking spaces\n- Aggressive behavior between shoppers\n- Potential property damage\n\n10. Online Scams and Fraudulent Deals\n- Fake websites\n- Misleading advertisements\n- Financial fraud targeting consumers\n\nThese incidents highlight potential dangers during Black Friday shopping events.",
